programme.title: The Battle At Lake Changjin

programme.title: Lan Kwai Fong

programme.title: A Cool Fish
programme.desc: In this dark-comedy, cop-turned-security guard Ma faces the ultimate challenge when his boss mysteriously disappears and his paralyzed sister makes a morbid deal with the armed bandits who abduct her.

programme.title: Lost Love
programme.desc: Mei tries to get over the death of her young son by becoming a foster parent. For 13 years, Mei's dedication to the foster child leads her to neglect her husband and the true needs of the child.

programme.title: Life Must Go On
programme.desc: When the 'midnight gymnasium' programme for wayward teenage girls is at funding risk, social worker Yanki puts together a dodgeball team to compete in a match and save it.

programme.title: Far Far Away
programme.desc: A 28-year-old IT geek has only been in love once. Surprisingly, he ends up getting romantically involved with five different women this year and they all live in far flung areas of Hong Kong.

programme.title: New Kung Fu Cult Master 2
programme.desc: The quest for the Dragon Sabre continues as Wu Ji and his three girlfriends set sail for Ice and Fire Island. After a series of vicious fights, they finally unveil the secret behind the Heaven Sword and Dragon Sabre.

programme.title: Where The Wind Blows
programme.desc: Detectives Lui Lok and Nam Kong build a corruption system that creates conflicts between the triad and the police. When ICAC hunts down the two, their control finally comes to an end.

programme.title: My Kickass Wife
programme.desc: Jade is a beautiful royal guard who is set up for marriage by the Queen in order to avoid the King setting eyes on her. Jade falls for Sean and helps him win the contest for her.

programme.title: I'm Livin' It
programme.desc: Once a successful banker, Bowen now spends his nights in a 24-hour fast food joint where he meets a group of homeless people. Together they strive to get themselves out of rock bottom.

programme.title: Call Me Agent
programme.desc: One day, Miu Ling rescues an injured secret agent who promises to make her his apprentice. From then on, her life is turned upside down and she goes onto a roller-coaster of madcap adventures.

programme.title: Somewhere Winter
programme.desc: The film follows the love story of a university student, An Ran and a Taiwanese man, Qi Xiao. They met and fell in love with each other in Beijing in 1991, at a concert by Chyi Chin, a Taiwanese singer.

programme.title: Unleashed
programme.desc: Fok Kit is the hottest underground boxer with unbeatable records. To save their boxing studio from being sold, he must win the fight against Sholin who is known as 'Killing Machine'.

programme.title: The Calling Of A Bus Driver
programme.desc: This is based on an inspiring true story about a girl named Suki who fulfills her dream of being a bus driver after breaking up with her boyfriend, who has an affair with her good friend.

programme.title: Come Back Home
programme.desc: In a chilly winter, De and his family goes on a self-drive tour to Changbai Mountain. The holiday turns tragic when De's eight-year-old son goes missing.

programme.title: A Guilty Conscience
programme.desc: Due to his negligence, sharp-tongued barrister Adrian's client is sentenced to 17 years in jail. In order to right his wrong, he must fight against one of the most powerful families in Hong Kong.

programme.title: Flashover
programme.desc: A sudden earthquake hits the gas pipes in an industrial park, triggering massive explosions and engulfing the neighboring area in flames. Firefighters must fight against the flames to safeguard lives with their own.

programme.title: Lion Rock
programme.desc: David Ki, one of the top rock climbers in Asia, lost everything when a motorcycle accident took away his ability to walk. Rather than succumbing to his fate, David found his own way of scaling the dizzying peaks again.

programme.title: The Infernal Walker
programme.desc: Ting is an undercover police who infiltrates a triad and Tuen is a triad mole being planted into the police force. While Ting is tired of being an undercover cop, Tuen wishes to quit the triad and become a real police.

programme.title: The Captain
programme.desc: The movie is based on the true story of Sichuan Airlines Flight 8633 incident on 14 May 2018. When the cockpit windshield shatters after takeoff, the Captain manages to land the airplane safely.

programme.title: Forbidden Tales Of Two Cities
programme.desc: Amorous complications and modern morals are just the beginning in Macau, where a love quartet is the source for sexy merriment.

programme.title: The Brave Archer 3
programme.desc: Guo Jing and Huang Rong go to Iron Palm Peak to search for the Book of Wumu. The chief of Iron Palm discovers their visit, and seriously injures Huang.

programme.title: The Mighty One
programme.desc: The famed Ivy Ling Po stars as a mysterious swordswoman dedicated to keeping the five volume 'Five Generations Fighting Methods' kung-fu manual out of evil-doer's hands.

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung And The...
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung meets a famous courtesan in Suzhou and in order to spend as much time as possible with her, he builds a direct underground tunnel into the Forbidden City.

programme.title: Clan Of The White Lotus
programme.desc: The head of White Lotus Clan, Lo, is a highly skilled martial artist who supports the Qing government and helps destroy the rebellion group.

programme.title: The Mirror And The Lichee
programme.desc: The curious title refers to two props that signal a happy beginning to what develops into a tragic love story between the scholar and a local beauty.

programme.title: The Delightful Forest
programme.desc: Imprisoned for murdering his sister-in-law, hero Wu Sung meets prison officer Tien Ching and a friendship is formed that may help save the guard's restaurant from thugs.

programme.title: Two Con Men
programme.desc: A wonderfully twisted, pseudo-romantic comedy starring Liang Tien and Chang Ying in an age-old competition between rookie con artist versus the ultimate, experienced flimflam man.

programme.title: The Avenging Eagle
programme.desc: One of the most beloved martial arts dramas of all-time chronicles the Thirteen Eagles Assassination Sect of the Iron Boat clan and the formidable warriors united by tragedy.

programme.title: Pale Passion
programme.desc: Chiang Li-ping plays a scorned wife Ah Hsia in an unsettling tale about cheating, adultery and blatant abuse, which develops into a deadly love triangle.

programme.title: Invincible Shaolin
programme.desc: While North Shaoliners fighting against the South Shaoliners, an evil Qing warlord wants to take over the world.

programme.title: Double Bliss
programme.desc: Ching Li stars in the story of two students looking to persuade their parents to bless their marriage. The lovebirds hatch what they think is a foolproof plan: they play dead!

programme.title: The Rescue
programme.desc: A group of Song survivors band together to save their prime minister from the encroaching Yuan forces. However, two heroes are imprisoned and must either escape or lose their lives!

programme.title: Call Of The Sea
programme.desc: A young fisherman, Chin Hu is in love with his childhood friend Hsiao Yu. However, the only son of a town bully lusts after Hsiao Yu's beauty and tries all possible ways to approach her.

programme.title: The King Boxer
programme.desc: This tale of a honorable fighter's retraining in the 'Iron Palm' style, that became the first international martial arts movie hit and made a continent-spanning star of Lo Lieh.

programme.title: When The Clouds Roll By
programme.desc: A schizophrenic who refuses to believe her pilot lover was killed and believes his death to be a lie created to end their relationship.

programme.title: The New One-Armed Swordsman
programme.desc: David Chiang leaps into action as all-new one-armed hero when the love of his life is kidnapped and his best friend is murdered by a gang hiding out on Tiger Mountain.

programme.title: The Bride Napping
programme.desc: A rich girl Yue Ying, together with her maid Chun Lan, encounter a poor scholar Bian Ji at a fete. Chun Lan realizes Yue Ying is in love with him, but mixes his identity with a bandit due to an old servant's confusion.

programme.title: The Invincible Fist
programme.desc: A dedicated chief constable nicknamed 'The Invincible Fist' is chasing after a band of bandits near a village one day and encounters an innocent blind girl.

programme.title: The Singing Escort
programme.desc: The music and magic of The Singing Escort is a great showcase for Betty Ting Pei's on-screen appeal. Ting playing Susan, a young woman hiding from her father.

programme.title: Golden Swallow
programme.desc: A heroine finds herself in a love triangle with a swordsman and a warrior. They team up to conquer the evil forces of the martial arts world.

programme.title: The Big Sting
programme.desc: Three buddies find a rare artifact known as the Double-Faced God but are poisoned by Lady Wu who steals the treasure from them. Before they die, they get their wives to promise to train their children to take it back.

programme.title: Four Riders
programme.desc: Four martial arts experts live in Seoul after the Korean War in the 1950s. One of them inexplicably crosses path with a drug trafficking syndicate, and his three friends have no choice but to fight on his side.

programme.title: Love Without End
programme.desc: Lin Dai stars as a nightclub singer who falls for a young architect. When he suffers grave financial difficulty, she does the unthinkable to help him.

programme.title: The Spiritual Boxer
programme.desc: Wang Yu is a fake ghost catcher whose deficient skills make him ill-equipped to fend off the irritable townsfolk. When he doublecrosses a local gangster, he is forced to fight.

programme.title: Mist Over Dream Lake
programme.desc: Yen Chun directs and stars in a heartwarming drama about a young girl, Chen whose parents send her to a relative's farm for an unforgettable summer.

programme.title: Duel For Gold
programme.desc: Three pairs of cunning male and female crooks trying to steal a million gold taels from the Fu Lai Treasury House.

programme.title: Facets Of Love
programme.desc: Set in the Ming Dynasty, the story revolves around a brothel and the girls who work there. The girl from a poor family, who is sold by her mother to the brothel and she hopes to escape this sad way of life one day.

programme.title: The Daredevils
programme.desc: Corrupt general Wang Li assumes power by killing his superior. The son of the murdered superior befriends four street performers called 'The Venoms', and they help him take revenge.

programme.title: Tragic Commitment
programme.desc: Alex is happily married to a gynecologist, Tung for five years. When Alex is fatally wounded in an accident, he feels obliged to tell Tung about his affair with Blackie.

programme.title: The Merry Wife
programme.desc: Li Ching, a 17-year-old girl who marries her 35-year-old teacher. Comedy ensues when Li decides to go to the same school with her husband but attempting to hide their relationship.

programme.title: Clan Of Amazons

programme.title: Gossip Street

programme.title: The Black Falcon

programme.title: Puppy Love

programme.title: Ambush
programme.desc: Ambush sees officer of the law Wan Chao Fan and his father being framed for a robbery they did not commit.

programme.title: Love With The Perfect Stranger
programme.desc: After breaking up with his girlfriend, salesman Bao meets a rich girl, Jin Jin, who just broke up with her boyfriend. Two equally heartbroken strangers fall in love instantly and get married on impulse.

programme.title: The Black Butterfly
programme.desc: Waitress Kwan leads a double life as moralistic outlaw, Black Butterfly. When she steals a cache of gold from the Five Devils Rock bandits, she soon has the government on her tail.

programme.title: My Name Ain't Suzie
programme.desc: Young Mei Li works as a bar girl in Wanchai to make a living. When she meets Jimmy in the bar, she thinks he is her true love and falls crazily in love with him. When Jimmy has to leave, Mei Li is devastated.

programme.desc: After marrying into a Japanese martial arts family, our Chinese hero inadvertently insults them all, leading to a number of stand-offs as he must fight to defend Chinese kung-fu.

programme.title: Intimate Confessions Of A...

programme.title: Hex
programme.desc: A sickly wife and maid conspire to kill her beastly husband, leading to a string of spooky twists and turns.

programme.title: Killers On Wheels
programme.desc: Kuo Ching-chung, an office worker, his wife, Chen Mei-chuan and his sister, Carrie, are passengers on a ferry bound for an outlying island of Hong Kong.

programme.title: Shaolin Abbot
programme.desc: The Monk Chi San is sent by his Shaolin masters to learn a special kung fu from a Wu-Tang priest and befriends his niece Wu Mei.

programme.title: The Scandalous Warlord
programme.desc: General Feng occupies the city of Shandong, and soldiers and civilians alike welcome him without knowing his tyrannical and lustful nature.

programme.title: The Vengeful Beauty

programme.title: The Comedy Of Mismatches

programme.desc: Ching Feng-Hsiao disguises herself as male to enroll for the imperial examination in order to save her lover from being framed by her stepmother. Can she make it?

programme.title: Return Of Reincarnated...
programme.desc: A band of ruthless ninjas slaughters the entire Wu Dong clan and frames Du Gu Wu Di, chief of the Invincible Clan, for the deed. Yun Fei Yang masters the silkworm martial arts style and takes revenge on Wu Di.
